Based in Bassett, VA, Bassett Furniture Industries, Inc. is a furniture retail company, with a presence at over 100 retail locations across the United States, Puerto Rico, and Canada. Established in 1902, the company is also expanding its online presence through… MoreBased in Bassett, VA, Bassett Furniture Industries, Inc. is a furniture retail company, with a presence at over 100 retail locations across the United States, Puerto Rico, and Canada. Established in 1902, the company is also expanding its online presence through an online furniture shopping catalog at www.bassettfurniture.com.
Based in Bassett, VA, Bassett Furniture Industries, Inc. is a furniture retail company, with a presence at over 100 retail locations across the United States, Puerto Rico, and Canada. Established in 1902, the company is also expanding its online presence through… MoreBased in Bassett, VA, Bassett Furniture Industries, Inc. is a furniture retail company, with a presence at over 100 retail locations across the United States, Puerto Rico, and Canada. Established in 1902, the company is also expanding its online presence through an online furniture shopping catalog at www.bassettfurniture.com.

The small IT department for Bassett Furniture Industries, Inc. is largely focused on manufacturing, ERP, and retail support. The major IT focus for the company through early or mid-2013 is expected to be an ERP systems migration to a new JDE platform. The department is divided into several small groups, including the Data Center Operations team utilizing IBM systems and the Application Development group focusing on Oracle and JDE applications. The IT Operations division is the largest group, with responsibilities including network systems, project management, and the IT help desk. Other responsibilities of this group are systems support and IT security.

The company is not currently interested in BYOD. Bassett Furniture Industries makes some use of outside service providers, including SysArc.

IT Intelligence Snippets :
2013 :
• 10-25 tb data volume company-wide across 1 to 2 data centers, and expects an annual data growth of 1-5%.
• 25-49% of its servers are to be virtualized by the end of 2013.
• Corporate IT manages 150 mobile devices.
• Corporate IT manages 775 desktops.
• Standardized on 1-2 product vendors with a limited set of hardware.
• Data center strategy is centered on virtualizing x86 servers for most applications; standalone servers or mainframes for business critical applications, and standardizing on rack-mount x86 systems and virtualized servers.
• Long term plan for running new applications is to add servers and virtualize, but no new facilities are scheduled.





